body of the necro that she has just slain.  Hum.   This is not a good sign when these ancient necros start prowling about raising armys.  Humm now if those fools can keep from getting Lady Mysticcat's husband dead it will be a good thing.<br>
<br>
Suddenly Mysticcat  herself arrives above the battle.  <br>
<br>
Rhapsodey Giggles softly to herself with the appearance of Mysticcat.   <br>
<br>
Well Now that the Lady herself is here I Most definitely will not need to do anything she will definitely take great pleasure in setting those blasted undead  on  their ears. <br>
<br>
  Well then  I guess I should be off  to investigate this situation further.   As Rhapsodey quickly checks the body of the necro at her feet for any items that may assist her in her search she finds an ancient ring engraved with the symbol of unrest.   Interesting a ring of unrest.   Humm this  may be more than I can handle alone but I do not have time wait for my Sword Sister Reoki to return from the meeting she had with the High Shaman of her village.  <br>
<br>
Sigh   We live for the one we die for the one.  I guess I had better get going and see what is happening before this insanity gets worse.<br>
<br>
Rhapsodey Quickly stands and Pulls a small amulet out.  She quietly says some ancient words of power in an unknown tongue and a Portal opens before her.  She looks around quickly tears coming to her eyes from the destruction and death that lay about her.  I hope I can determine what is causing this and that I can stop it before anymore innocent people are harmed.  And with that she steps through the glowing portal that takes her to the lands of unrest.    <br>
